    "narrative": "The daily projections for Ghost Ride the WHIP highlight **Tyler Soderstrom** (76.84) and **Trevor Story** (73.82) as our primary offensive engines today. **Soderstrom** benefits from a massive park-adjusted ceiling and a favorable righty-righty matchup against Cecconi, while **Trevor Story** provides our highest ceiling due to a perfect storm of a weak arm in Arrighetti, a favorable wind, and a slow delivery profile that significantly boosts his stolen base potential\u2014a critical factor given our prioritization of speed. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (70.89) rounds out the top trio, as his platoon advantage against Hancock effectively offsets a poor park factor, assuming he locks into the projected 3-hole spot.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the final utility and middle infield spots, specifically leaving **Travis Bazzana** (46.50) on the bench despite his elite .408 xwOBA. While **Bazzana** flashed significant underlying talent, the Optimizer favored the stability of **Alex Freeland** and **Luis Campusano** due to the latter\u2019s defensive positional value and our current league-wide scarcity of roster slots. **Jose Caballero** also fell short of the starting cut, as his 39.32 efficiency rating\u2014penalized heavily by a difficult matchup against Bradish and a bottom-of-the-order placement\u2014dropped him below our 40.0 \"Below Floor\" threshold, keeping him stashed to preserve our valuable game caps.\n\nRisks remain present across the board, most notably with **Corbin Carroll** (64.74). While he is an elite talent, his matchup against a high-tier arm in Imanaga, combined with a significant platoon disadvantage and an opponent with a strong hold on the running game, suppresses what would otherwise be a 90+ rated day. We are also tracking a \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Vinnie Pasquantino**; should he be shifted down in the order or removed from the starting lineup entirely, we will need to pivot to the bench to maintain our 5x5 production floor. Despite these variables, the aggregate lineup provides a balanced mix of speed and power, positioning Ghost Ride the WHIP to maintain our momentum in a crowded standings field.",
